title: Ceiling Paper, 1905–15
description:
Floral motif with small two-flower bouquets inside a petal-like scroll pattern. Individual flowers in the resulting negative spaces. Between each floral motif is a row of either horizontal or vertical dots. Background has an overall layer of the same foliate motif. Ground is white. Printed in blues, greens, white mica and blue mica. 
Printed in selvedge: "21"

tombstone.epitaph:
Ceiling Paper, 1905–15.
1905–15. Machine-printed on paper, mica, liquid. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-1165.
